  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Adult subjects, 18 - 85 years old, who understand the risks and benefits of
             participation and have provided written informed consent for the study.

          2. Subjects who are experiencing a first event of CDI diagnosed within the last 10 days.

          3. Subjects who are medically stable.

          4. Subjects who are willing and able to comply with the study procedures and visit
             schedules outlined.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Subjects who are currently on treatment for a recurrence of CDI.

          2. Subjects who are currently or have recently been treated with immunoglobulin therapy.

          3. Pregnant or breast feeding females.

          4. Concurrent, acutely life-threatening diseases.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
